<h id='newSearchPage'><a href="http://w3future.com/weblog/2002/08/11.xml#a120" class="weblogItemTitle">New search page</a></h>
<p>My weblog archive page has been defunct for a while now. Today I replaced it with <a href="http://w3future.com/html/search.html">a dynamic search page</a>, which uses the Google web service through <a href="http://www.dentedreality.com.au/xoomle/">XooMLe</a>. The disadvantage of using Google is that it doesn't seem to return every possible result. But the advantages are that the results are ordered by relevance, and it shows the sentences that contain the search terms.</p>
